id: pm-9x1c
title: Add package-first command aliases and pm install
description: Expose package-first lifecycle commands while preserving extension command compatibility.
type: Task
status: closed
priority: 0
tags[4]: commands,install,packages,pm-cli
created_at: "2026-05-11T17:41:31.580Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-11T18:51:13.703Z"
author: codex-agent
acceptance_criteria: pm install installs package/extension sources; pm package and pm packages expose lifecycle subcommands; contracts/native integrations include package actions; command tests cover aliases.
parent: pm-59gj
resolution: "Implemented package-first command aliases and install support while preserving extension compatibility. Added pm install, pm package, and pm packages command surfaces; expanded SDK/Pi/MCP contracts; package-root discovery supports pm.extensions, Pi-compatible pi.extensions, conventional extension directories, and npm:<spec> sources via npm pack; docs and skills now route users through package-first terminology."
expected_result: "Users can install package sources through pm install and manage them through pm package/package aliases without breaking existing pm extension workflows; SDK, Pi wrapper, MCP, docs, and tests expose the package vocabulary."
actual_result: "Manual temp-project dogfood installed local pm.extensions and npm pi.extensions packages, pm package manage listed both installed extensions, SDK package-install/install contracts were present, linked tests passed, full release gates passed with 100% coverage, and telemetry/Sentry gate returned fresh actionable data."
comments[4]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-11T17:41:31.580Z",codex-agent,Child task created after Pi research showed install/package terminology is the user-facing model and existing pm extension manager can provide the first compatible implementation slice.
  "2026-05-11T18:02:29.269Z",codex-agent,"Progress: implemented package-first command surface (pm install, pm package, pm packages), SDK contract/native/MCP aliases, local package root discovery via pm.extensions/pi.extensions and conventional directories, npm:<spec> install through npm pack, docs/skills routing, and focused regression coverage. Verification so far: pnpm build passed; docs-skills gate passed; secret scan passed; focused package suite passed 4 files / 128 tests."
  "2026-05-11T18:40:36.879Z",codex-agent,"Observability check: patched Sentry gate console-noise filter for starter-extension success log. Live gate now passes with explicit historical thresholds (critical=1, high=2); telemetry required mode is fresh and ok with finish_error_rate_pct=4.2 and failures_without_error_code_rows=0. Remaining relevant Sentry issues are pre-existing PM-CLI-N (2026-05-10 extension import), PM-CLI-A and PM-CLI-9 (2026-05-08 embedding timeouts); PM-CLI-J is correctly counted as ignored starter console noise."
  "2026-05-11T18:51:07.768Z",codex-agent,"Final evidence: pm test pm-9x1c --run --progress passed all 3 linked checks; node scripts/release/run-gates.mjs --telemetry-mode required --max-sentry-critical 1 --max-sentry-high 2 passed build, typecheck, docs/skills, static quality, coverage 90 files/1278 tests with 100% coverage, version policy, secret scan, npx smoke, and Sentry/telemetry gate. pm health and validate remain warn-only for pre-existing history drift items pm-54d/pm-f3q4/pm-fdla/pm-mb4n/pm-tq1 and pre-existing missing resolution metadata on pm-dhie."
